# WiFi Packet Sniffer

This Python script captures WiFi packets and records information about them, including packet type, subtype, signal strength, source, destination, and more.

## Requirements

- Python 3
- Npcap (for Windows) or libpcap (for Linux)
- Scapy (Python library for packet manipulation)
      - pip install scapy


## Installation

1. Clone this repository to your local machine:

```shell
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/wifi-packet-sniffer.git

